cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with generative models of text and sentence compression. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a variational auto-encoder for inference. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves natural language processing and deep learning. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for sentence compression, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as CNNs are commonly used in image processing. Finally, the paper's use of semi-supervised learning could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
